# Sub-agents and parallel work

## Parallel Task / sub-agents

- Use parallel sub-agents only for **disjoint** domains (e.g. unrelated test files, non-overlapping paths).
- After parallel work, run **full** lint/test for every touched stack and resolve overlapping edits yourself.

## Prefer sequential

- **Auth, session, and security-hardening** slices: implement and review sequentially unless tasks are strictly isolated (separate packages or paths).
- **Same file or shared types:** never split one file across parallel agents.

## Prompts

- Sub-agent prompts must be self-contained (stack, paths, acceptance criteria).
- Never paste tokens, `.env` values, or production URLs into sub-agent prompts.
